comments.body:
Instead of module augmentations, why not have local types that extend the base types? e.g.

```
import { IncomingMessage as IncomingMessageBase, ServerResponse as ServerResponseBase } from 'http';

interface IncomingMessage extends IncomingMessageBase {
    log: Logger;
}

interface ServerResponse extends ServerResponseBase {
    err?: Error;
}
```

This way, you don't pollute the global scope.

